text_run.content: The Zilliz Cloud Bring Your Own Cloud (BYOC) solution offers a subscription model enabling you to deploy Zilliz Cloud services on your cloud infrastructure for enhanced security. This topic explores the BYOC license, emphasizing its usage, monitoring, and implications for users.
The calculation method for the Zilliz Cloud BYOC solution involves distinguishing between the control plane and the data plane.
functionality, Zilliz Cloud platform operations, data backup, migration, and alerts
cores consumed at the control plane are not deducted from the cores subscribed in the BYOC license
cores consumed at the data plane are deducted from the cores subscribed in your license

with core usage between 70-99% or validity under 60 days. Time to assess your future needs and prepare for action.

with core usage over 100% or license expiration. Critical to renew or upgrade now to avoid operational disruptions.

Contact our sales for help if you are in the yellow or red zone. We recommend you renew or upgrade your license before it expires or reaches its limit to avoid restrictions like the inability to create new clusters or scale up.
To prevent service disruptions, renew or upgrade your license if it is approaching
expiration or nearing the core usage limit

Zilliz Cloud simultaneously keeps track of your license's validity period and core usage, and applies restrictions accordingly if your license expires while cores are overused.
Potential consequences of failing to renew or upgrade
Failing to renew or upgrade within the
grace period results in your Zilliz Cloud account being frozen and service access revoked. The following operations are prohibited once frozen:
Creating, restarting, stopping, or scaling clusters
Managing collections or indexes through the web console or SDKs
